{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8494e30c-3163-4506-af23-873562ebadf5","content":"Here's what to change for migrating NUnit to Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n**1. Update package references in your `.csproj`:**\n\n```xml\n<!-- Remove these -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"NUnit3TestAdapter\" Version=\"4.6.0\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk\" Version=\"...\" />\n\n<!-- Add this -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"NUnit.Runner\" Version=\"...\" />\n```\n\n**2. Add these properties to your `.csproj`:**\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n  <EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatform>true</EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatform>\n  <!-- For dotnet test compatibility: -->\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**3. Keep** your `NUnit` package reference and all existing test code — no test changes needed.\n\n**Key differences after migration:**\n- Tests run as a standalone executable (hence `Exe` output type)\n- `dotnet test` still works (with the `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property)\n- You can also run the test binary directly: `./MyTests.exe`","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9dfe4d5b-cefd-417e-9293-a5482c3e5b9a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing infrastructure - I don't need to search a codebase for this. Let me provide a concise answer.\n\nKey changes needed to migrate NUnit from VSTest (NUnit3TestAdapter + Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n1. Replace `NUnit3TestAdapter` with `NUnit.Engine` (or the appropriate adapter for Microsoft.Testing.Platform)\n2. Actually, for Microsoft.Testing.Platform with NUnit, you need to use `NUnitTesting.Extensions.Microsoft.Testing.Platform` or similar.\n\n\n3. Remove the old VSTest packages and add the Microsoft.Testing.Platform NUnit extension, then enable the platform in the project file with the appropriate property flags.\n\nActually, I need to be more precise about the package names—the exact NUnit package for Microsoft.Testing.Platform might be `NUnit.Testing.Platform` or a similar variant, and I should verify what the correct migration path looks like for MSTest as well. For NUnit, I need to remove the `NUnit3TestAdapter` and `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` packages, then add `NUnit.Runner` to get Microsoft.Testing.Platform support, while also setting the project to output as an executable and enabling the testing platform entry point generation.\n\nThe next step is either letting the auto-generated entry point handle things or manually creating a `Program.cs` file if needed.","outputTokens":1255,"requestId":"5C38:19AB05:84291:A4783:69F549EE"},"id":"8ce91a03-58eb-44f1-abc4-5d51f52b6af9","timestamp":"2026-05-02T00:49:08.025Z","parentId":"0c4b89e1-f72e-4cd3-9bd1-362df82b7cb6"}
